	<tr>
		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Post subject:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b>Nestopia's back from the dead</b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Hey boys and girls, I just wanted to let you all know I decided to resurrect Nestopia awhile ago. It's one of my personal favourite emulators, and I didn't want to see it die, so I forked it and have been making whatever improvements I can as a service to the community. Most of what I've done is related to the Linux release, but I have also done some stuff for the win32 release and added some patches from members of the community to the core emulator. There's a bit of community involvement from the libretro team as well.<br /><br />Anyways, if anyone has patches or improvements, feel free to throw them my way. I'm planning to keep maintaining this code for everyone's benefit. You may have seen Windows builds on emucr from my repo, and if you're a unixy type of person, the packages in Debian, Arch, and OpenBSD are also from my repo.<br /><br /><a href="https://github.com/rdanbrook/nestopia" class="postlink">Github Repo</a>

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


