		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Post subject:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b>Re: Nestopia's back from the dead</b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" /><div class="quotetitle"><b>Quote:</b></div><div class="quotecontent">1. What does adjust pitch do in sound settings?</div><br />When you set custom speed (30 FPS for example) DPCM pitch drop down, while other 4 channels stay on standard pitch.<br />But if you set &quot;adjust pitch&quot; on, other 4 channels drop pitch down according to DPCM.<br /><br />Listen Journey to Silius or Gremlins 2 for test it!<br /><br /><img src="http://savepic.org/3545799.png" alt="Image" /><br /><br />Guys, try to help me please:<br />Dendy emulation incorrect in official 1.40 because something is broken since 1.38:<br /><div class="quotetitle"><b>Quote:</b></div><div class="quotecontent">v.1.38 changes:<br />- PPU power/reset timing and register states. <br />- Misc IRQ/NMI/BRK/DMA special-case behavior.</div><br />I've compiled 1.36, 1.37, 1.38, 1.39 and 1.40 versions of NEStopia and &quot;hacked&quot; their PAL-mode according to Dendy-timings:<br /><div class="codetitle"><b>Code:</b></div><div class="codecontent">fragments of NstBase.hpp (NstCpu.hpp &amp; NstPpu.hpp under version 1.37)<br />// fixing PAL(RP2A07) divider to dendy CPU(UA6527P) divider<br />{<br />&nbsp;RP2A03_CC = 12,<br />&nbsp;RP2A07_CC = 15<br />};<br /><br />// fixing timings according to dendy PPU(UA6538)<br />&nbsp; &nbsp;RP2C07_VACTIVE&nbsp; &nbsp;= 240,<br />&nbsp; &nbsp;RP2C07_VSLEEP&nbsp; &nbsp; = 51,<br />&nbsp; &nbsp;RP2C07_VINT&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; = 20,<br />&nbsp; &nbsp;RP2C07_VDUMMY&nbsp; &nbsp; = 1,<br /><br />Fragments of NstApu.cpp<br />// also fixing Noise and DMC PAL-rates according to NTSC-tables<br />&nbsp;... blabla<br />&nbsp;... blabla<br />// end<br /></div><br /><br />But strange glitches <a href="http://img18.imageshack.us/gal.php?g=otherb.png" class="postlink">appear</a> since version 1.38 and above:<br />below v1.38 these glitches <a href="http://img265.imageshack.us/gal.php?g=battletoadsdoubledragonu.png" class="postlink">aren't present</a> (it is correct and very similar to hardware):<br /><br />How to fix it in nestopia undead?<br />Here is <a href="http://sourceforge.net/projects/nestopia/files/Nestopia/" class="postlink">1.31-1.40</a> source archives.<br />And here is dendy <a href="http://savepic.su/2652378.htm" class="postlink">information</a>.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


